WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.445 --> 00:00:04.335
And I've been surfing
ever since I can remember.

2
00:00:05.965 --> 00:00:08.585
It's hard to imagine my life
when I wasn't surfing.

3
00:00:09.055 --> 00:00:12.185
I want to get out of here,
and this is my ticket out.

4
00:00:12.585 --> 00:00:15.535
I'm really good, man.
I'm the best on the island.

5
00:00:15.935 --> 00:00:21.785
I know it sounds cocky for saying that,
but, I mean, I am, like the best.

6
00:00:28.825 --> 00:00:31.585
I was born and raised here in Shiverpool.

7
00:00:33.565 --> 00:00:35.325
Lived here my whole life.

8
00:00:35.895 --> 00:00:39.525
That's where they sort the fish. It's
the dumbest thing I've ever heard of.

9
00:00:39.705 --> 00:00:44.574
But yeah, I worked there
just to pacify my mom a little bit.

10
00:00:45.304 --> 00:00:47.464
Good old Shiverpool.

11
00:00:48.814 --> 00:00:50.244
This place sucks, bro.

12
00:00:50.884 --> 00:00:54.974
I worked my way up from the sardine
pile, then to the mackerel pile...

13
00:00:55.154 --> 00:00:56.984
...and I ended up
on the gefilte fish pile.

14
00:00:57.154 --> 00:00:59.454
- All hard work.
- Not like some I could mention.

15
00:00:59.624 --> 00:01:01.814
Yes, this farkakte kid
with the thing on the water.

16
00:01:02.324 --> 00:01:03.384
My house?

17
00:01:03.564 --> 00:01:05.724
Over there. You see it
right there with the surfboards?

18
00:01:06.564 --> 00:01:09.934
Yeah, I just live here with me
and my brother, Glen, my mom.

19
00:01:11.034 --> 00:01:13.264
He was a little, teeny, small egg.

20
00:01:14.734 --> 00:01:16.174
He wasn't very impressive.

21
00:01:16.334 --> 00:01:18.334
Glen was the big egg,
Cody was the small egg.

22
00:01:19.074 --> 00:01:21.504
He can't help it.
That's just the way he is.

23
00:01:21.674 --> 00:01:22.774
I mean, he's out there...

24
00:01:24.114 --> 00:01:27.574
...in the water all day
shirking his responsibilities.

25
00:01:27.954 --> 00:01:31.404
You know, hatching these eggs
is a big responsibility.

26
00:01:31.624 --> 00:01:33.884
And my brother, Cody,
he just doesn't understand that.

27
00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:38.684
- He needs to step up and be a man.
- It takes a real man to sit on an egg.

28
00:01:38.864 --> 00:01:41.834
- You know it.
- Quincy, come to Daddy.

29
00:01:41.994 --> 00:01:44.275
He wants to be different.
All the time with the different.

30
00:01:44.334 --> 00:01:45.734
Who's got the time in the day to...

31
00:01:45.864 --> 00:01:47.354
Only six months in a day.

32
00:01:47.534 --> 00:01:49.494
- Thanks for making it.
- Sorry. It was too good to miss.

33
00:01:49.504 --> 00:01:51.974
- Thanks for making it.
- How was it out there?

34
00:01:52.144 --> 00:01:53.904
He's the big brother.
I'm the little brother.

35
00:01:54.274 --> 00:01:55.864
I'm not touching you.

36
00:01:56.044 --> 00:01:57.644
- Not gonna touch you.
- Do you see this?

37
00:01:57.714 --> 00:01:58.974
- Don't. Please?
- I'm not.

38
00:01:59.144 --> 00:02:00.514
He makes sure that I know that.

39
00:02:00.954 --> 00:02:04.444
I had to fight for everything.
Even Mom's tuna casserole.

40
00:02:11.663 --> 00:02:12.753
I'm lucky I survived.

41
00:02:12.923 --> 00:02:15.953
It really wasn't that easy
for him growing up.

42
00:02:16.563 --> 00:02:18.193
Like I said before...

43
00:02:19.263 --> 00:02:21.463
...he never really knew his father.

44
00:02:24.373 --> 00:02:28.533
I'm not really the person to ask about it
because I was too young to remember.

45
00:02:28.713 --> 00:02:31.303
Look, I'm not the only kid on the island...

46
00:02:31.483 --> 00:02:35.003
...whose dad was, you know, eaten.

47
00:02:35.713 --> 00:02:40.983
- Still, it had to be traumatic.
- No. Not for me, bro. Not for me.

48
00:02:42.423 --> 00:02:45.583
- What's your dream?
- To go away.

49
00:02:46.323 --> 00:02:49.763
- To go away. That's great.
- Do you guys want a drink?

50
00:02:49.933 --> 00:02:52.993
Got to run away
from responsibility and life.

51
00:02:53.163 --> 00:02:54.433
This is unique.

52
00:02:54.603 --> 00:02:56.793
- This is not the norm.
- "I have dreams."

53
00:02:58.173 --> 00:03:01.003
- When is this not happening?
- Don't make that noise.

54
00:03:03.073 --> 00:03:05.173
- Cody!
- It's really disrespectful.

55
00:03:06.213 --> 00:03:07.543
I would never do that.

56
00:03:09.613 --> 00:03:11.343
You just wouldn't make it
out of your mouth.

57
00:03:11.523 --> 00:03:13.183
That's the difference between you and me.

58
00:03:13.383 --> 00:03:15.613
You know what?
I can't do this anymore.

59
00:03:15.793 --> 00:03:17.023
Mom. Look what you did.

60
00:03:17.193 --> 00:03:19.553
This is for me. This isn't for you.
Why is Glen still here?

61
00:03:19.723 --> 00:03:22.253
Oh, yeah, exactly. Mom!

62
00:03:22.433 --> 00:03:24.363
I don't understand why
everybody's so judgmental.

63
00:03:24.533 --> 00:03:26.723
I understand why Mom's judgmental.

64
00:03:26.903 --> 00:03:30.462
I think it's because she cares,
partially. It's also partially because...

65
00:03:30.642 --> 00:03:33.202
...everyone else is looking at her like,
"Hey, Cody's just a bum.

66
00:03:33.302 --> 00:03:35.702
Cody's this. Cody's that.
Cody's this."

67
00:03:36.372 --> 00:03:38.932
Cody's me, bro. Let me be me.

68
00:03:39.582 --> 00:03:41.272
When is that gonna start?

69
00:03:53.792 --> 00:03:56.622
You know what they call me?
The dream maker. The dream maker.

70
00:03:58.032 --> 00:04:00.002
I find these kids, I bring them here...

71
00:04:00.162 --> 00:04:03.402
...and I give them a chance
to be somebody.

72
00:04:04.502 --> 00:04:07.372
You know my greatest joy
as a surf promoter? Finding Z.

73
00:04:07.542 --> 00:04:09.012
Watching him rise to the top.

74
00:04:09.172 --> 00:04:13.412
I still can't believe he's gone.
He was like a son to me, you know?

75
00:04:13.582 --> 00:04:17.342
It was a heart thing, you know?
Can we just take five minutes?

76
00:04:17.582 --> 00:04:20.682
How's my hair? Is it messed up?
I ain't got all day. Is it mussed?

77
00:04:20.852 --> 00:04:22.652
We just have a few more questions
about Big Z.

78
00:04:22.722 --> 00:04:24.522
But right now
I think we're more interested...

79
00:04:24.592 --> 00:04:26.962
...in the Reggie Belafonte story,
and who could blame us?

80
00:04:27.132 --> 00:04:28.852
But Big Z is kind of the focus of our...

81
00:04:29.032 --> 00:04:30.932
Let's get the coconut filler guy over here.

82
00:04:31.102 --> 00:04:32.722
And how about the guy sweeping the sand?

83
00:04:32.902 --> 00:04:36.702
Can we hear your boring story
about your tedious, ridiculous life?

84
00:04:36.872 --> 00:04:38.562
Get your feathers off it! Stop!

85
00:04:38.772 --> 00:04:40.702
I ain't got all day.
I got a big production here.

86
00:04:40.872 --> 00:04:42.032
Roll, okay? Just roll!

87
00:04:42.442 --> 00:04:46.432
Welcome, fans, to another edition
of SPEN Sports.

88
00:04:46.882 --> 00:04:48.242
This is Sal Masakela...

89
00:04:48.412 --> 00:04:52.751
...and we're here at the surfing capital
of the world, Pen Gu Island...

90
00:04:52.921 --> 00:04:57.221
...for a preview of the tenth annual
Big Z Memorial Surf-Off.

91
00:04:58.221 --> 00:05:00.281
Professional surfers extraordinaire...

92
00:05:00.461 --> 00:05:02.321
...Kelly and Rob tell us...

93
00:05:02.491 --> 00:05:04.891
...what challenges
our surfers are going to face.

94
00:05:06.301 --> 00:05:08.901
First things first, Sal. The wave.
It's the perfect combination...

95
00:05:09.001 --> 00:05:13.461
...of beauty and danger. Even
the pros are terrified of this place.

96
00:05:15.511 --> 00:05:16.671
Hi, Mom.

97
00:05:16.841 --> 00:05:18.371
Dig this, Sal. Section behind me.

98
00:05:19.711 --> 00:05:22.031
It's "The Boneyards."
Few surfers have ventured in there...

99
00:05:22.181 --> 00:05:23.201
...and come out alive.

100
00:05:23.381 --> 00:05:25.981
Are you trying to tell me
people have died here?

101
00:05:26.151 --> 00:05:28.781
- That's right, Sal.
- A moment of silence for them.

102
00:05:28.951 --> 00:05:33.011
And we keep it moving because
if the Boneyards was not enough...

103
00:05:33.191 --> 00:05:37.091
...our surfers will be facing off with
Tank "The Shredder" Evans.

104
00:05:37.261 --> 00:05:40.091
Tank, nine-time defending champ.

105
00:05:40.901 --> 00:05:42.201
A role model? No.

106
00:05:43.701 --> 00:05:46.331
But I do consider myself somebody
that everyone should look up to.

107
00:05:46.501 --> 00:05:49.101
Kids should try to pretend
that they're Tank.

108
00:05:49.271 --> 00:05:51.741
I mean, they should try.
Good luck, kids.

109
00:05:52.681 --> 00:05:55.241
You never want to get in there
and help them out...

110
00:05:55.411 --> 00:05:59.141
...and show them how to surf
and spend some time with the kids?

111
00:05:59.321 --> 00:06:00.981
No, I don't want to do that.

112
00:06:01.151 --> 00:06:03.381
- Anyway, this is my wave.
- Always classy Tank Evans.

113
00:06:03.551 --> 00:06:06.281
Coming up after the break,
penguin dodge ball. Stick around.

114
00:06:07.731 --> 00:06:11.061
Okay, to get back to the competition,
I just want to say:

115
00:06:11.231 --> 00:06:14.161
I'm scouring the globe
for the next big thing.

116
00:06:14.501 --> 00:06:15.860
But that's another story.

117
00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:22.030
He doesn't look for them.
I find them.

118
00:06:23.410 --> 00:06:25.010
I find these penguins.
I find the talent.

119
00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:28.000
Reggie has sent me everywhere on this trip.

120
00:06:28.110 --> 00:06:29.600
Anyplace there's an ocean...

121
00:06:30.950 --> 00:06:32.580
...a lake, a puddle.
It's ridiculous.

122
00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:36.720
I am on so much migraine medication,
you have no idea.

123
00:06:36.890 --> 00:06:40.050
The stress is killing me. I don't know
how much longer I can last.

124
00:06:40.220 --> 00:06:42.220
I have to tell you that right now.

125
00:06:45.130 --> 00:06:47.290
You gotta try this blowhole thing, man.

126
00:06:47.470 --> 00:06:49.730
This whale dude
is giving me a brain freeze.

127
00:06:52.400 --> 00:06:53.870
I lost a bet.

128
00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:56.600
Excuse me. Excuse me.

129
00:06:56.770 --> 00:07:00.230
Does anybody
in this entire frozen wasteland surf?

130
00:07:00.410 --> 00:07:03.040
- The Cody Maverick kid does that.
- Wonderful. Thank you.

131
00:07:03.250 --> 00:07:05.220
You know, you're sitting on...
thin ice.

132
00:07:05.380 --> 00:07:08.510
Excuse me, I'm looking for...
I'm looking for Cody Maverick.

133
00:07:08.690 --> 00:07:12.320
- Has anyone seen Cody Maverick?
- I'm Cody Maverick.

134
00:07:13.760 --> 00:07:16.920
Mike Abromowitz from the Big Z
Memorial Surf-Off, Pen Gu Island.

135
00:07:17.090 --> 00:07:19.050
You came here on a wha...
You came to see me. Wow!

136
00:07:19.100 --> 00:07:23.190
- Quite a slip-and-slider, aren't you?
- You're here. What an honor, sir.

137
00:07:23.370 --> 00:07:25.730
Lovely. Wonderful. I hear you surf.

138
00:07:25.900 --> 00:07:27.660
- Is this true?
- You gotta see what I can do.

139
00:07:27.670 --> 00:07:29.530
- You can actually stand on a board?
- I'll be back.

140
00:07:29.540 --> 00:07:31.900
You're gonna see what I can do
everything's gonna be good...

141
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:34.400
...and I'm coming with you.
- I can't imagine a better day.

142
00:07:34.580 --> 00:07:38.609
Ma! Ma, he came... the scout.
Mikey. He came. He's here.

143
00:07:38.779 --> 00:07:41.449
- What? Yeah.
- He's giving me a shot now, Ma.

144
00:07:41.619 --> 00:07:43.179
You want to come watch me surf?

145
00:07:43.349 --> 00:07:45.289
- No, that's okay.
- Just this time.

146
00:07:45.459 --> 00:07:50.259
- I'm busy. I'm chopping here.
- Okay. All right, well, wish me luck.

147
00:07:50.429 --> 00:07:53.729
Cody, just be careful of those big waves.

148
00:07:56.629 --> 00:07:58.689
Well, anytime now.

149
00:07:59.039 --> 00:08:03.169
You should have been here yesterday.
We had a sweet swell yesterday.

150
00:08:03.339 --> 00:08:06.309
I was doing some layback 360s
and floaters. It was insane.

151
00:08:06.479 --> 00:08:07.809
Wow! Start the whale.

152
00:08:07.979 --> 00:08:09.909
No! Wait! Wait!
Just give me one more chance.

153
00:08:10.079 --> 00:08:11.909
- All I need is one, please.
- You just had it.

154
00:08:11.919 --> 00:08:13.849
- Dude, please don't go.
- Tough break, kid.

155
00:08:14.019 --> 00:08:16.379
- Just wait one second.
- Better luck next year. Move it.

156
00:08:16.549 --> 00:08:19.489
- Let's go. He's coming!
- Just one wave. That's all I need.

157
00:08:20.089 --> 00:08:23.579
I've never won anything my whole life.

158
00:08:24.929 --> 00:08:27.359
Just once I want to feel like a winner.

159
00:08:27.829 --> 00:08:31.929
I used to scout songbirds. Toucans
for this musical revue in Brazil.

160
00:08:32.099 --> 00:08:34.369
Now that's show business.
Toucans...

161
00:08:34.539 --> 00:08:35.599
Hold on!

162
00:08:36.609 --> 00:08:39.369
I don't care what you say,
I'm coming to Pen Gu!

163
00:08:39.539 --> 00:08:44.379
No way, no how.
This is a contest for big-wave surfers.

164
00:08:44.549 --> 00:08:47.039
Can't this blubber ball go any faster?
Step on it, fish sticks!

165
00:08:48.949 --> 00:08:51.009
No, no, no, no!

166
00:08:55.959 --> 00:08:59.049
Poor kid. I feel bad a little bit.
Honestly, this is embar...

167
00:08:59.229 --> 00:09:00.699
No, wait! Wait!

168
00:09:12.508 --> 00:09:14.338
Did you guys see that?
He almost had my board!

169
00:09:15.308 --> 00:09:18.148
He almost had it.
Next time we'll get it.

170
00:09:18.318 --> 00:09:20.178
- Yeah, so anyway...
- Wait!

171
00:09:41.668 --> 00:09:44.938
We got you. We got you.
Oh, you are heavier than you look.

172
00:09:45.908 --> 00:09:47.168
- Man, we did it.
- Thank you.

173
00:09:47.348 --> 00:09:48.838
Teamwork always pays off.

174
00:09:49.008 --> 00:09:50.738
- I'm Chicken Joe, man.
- Thanks, Joe.

175
00:09:50.918 --> 00:09:54.278
Don't you ever, ever, do anything
like that in the contest, all right?

176
00:09:54.448 --> 00:09:55.708
- I'm in?
- Yeah, you're in.

177
00:09:55.888 --> 00:09:59.788
Because that was entertaining,
in a horrifying sort of way.

178
00:10:01.028 --> 00:10:02.518
Right on, dude.

179
00:10:03.728 --> 00:10:06.528
My name's Cody Maverick,
Shiverpool. You?

180
00:10:06.698 --> 00:10:09.028
No, I'm not from Shiverpool.

181
00:10:09.368 --> 00:10:12.958
- Where are you from?
- Dude, I'm from Lake Michigan.

182
00:10:13.138 --> 00:10:15.128
That's where I surf.
I was the only one...

183
00:10:16.608 --> 00:10:18.468
...around my town who did it.

184
00:10:18.678 --> 00:10:21.038
A lot of people thought
I was crazy, but I'm used to that.

185
00:10:21.208 --> 00:10:23.408
- I know how you feel, Joe.
- You do?

186
00:10:23.648 --> 00:10:26.277
- Yeah.
- Radical.

187
00:10:29.647 --> 00:10:33.047
- Butt freeze!
- Somebody help the chicken.

188
00:11:11.327 --> 00:11:12.917
Look out!

189
00:11:14.227 --> 00:11:16.197
Slater, Machado.
How's it going, bros?

190
00:11:16.367 --> 00:11:17.727
- Good. Thanks.
- What's up, buddy?

191
00:11:17.767 --> 00:11:19.497
Okay. Later, dudes.

192
00:11:20.437 --> 00:11:21.957
Radical.

193
00:11:42.927 --> 00:11:46.517
Dude, look where I'm standing.
I'm standing where Z stood.

194
00:11:48.296 --> 00:11:52.126
- Aw, man.
- Dude, you gotta try this.

195
00:11:52.296 --> 00:11:54.856
- No, I'm okay.
- Come on. Just one bite.

196
00:11:55.036 --> 00:11:57.366
All right. One bite, that's it.

197
00:11:58.736 --> 00:12:00.466
Yeah, yeah? What do you think?

198
00:12:00.636 --> 00:12:02.906
It's not bad.
It kind of tastes like chicken...

199
00:12:03.346 --> 00:12:05.246
Yep. What's chi-chi?

200
00:12:05.576 --> 00:12:08.636
Coming through! Oh, crap.

201
00:12:13.956 --> 00:12:16.426
Oh, man. I'm in love.

202
00:12:16.586 --> 00:12:19.646
Help me! I'm drowning!

203
00:12:22.896 --> 00:12:26.626
What are you standing here
next to me for? Go talk to her, man.

204
00:12:26.796 --> 00:12:28.836
- I'm not gonna talk to her.
- She's digging on you.

205
00:12:29.006 --> 00:12:30.126
- She called you crap.
- Joe.

206
00:12:30.266 --> 00:12:32.206
- Thanks again.
- All right, well...

207
00:12:32.376 --> 00:12:34.736
...this is the third time
you've been unconscious this week.

208
00:12:34.806 --> 00:12:36.726
I just don't think
it's very good for your brain.

209
00:12:36.806 --> 00:12:39.366
- I know. Bye, Lani.
- Okay.

210
00:12:39.976 --> 00:12:43.036
Yeah, that was awesome
how you saved his life and all.

211
00:12:43.216 --> 00:12:46.846
That was just unbelievable. Really.

212
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:51.246
You here for the surf contest?

213
00:12:52.026 --> 00:12:56.226
- Well, I'll be watching you.
- Really? You'll be watching me?

214
00:12:56.396 --> 00:12:58.026
Well, yeah, from the lifeguard station.

215
00:12:58.196 --> 00:13:00.496
- Yeah. Right.
- It's my job.

216
00:13:00.666 --> 00:13:02.796
- That's your job.
- Are you gonna kiss her?

217
00:13:02.966 --> 00:13:04.996
- What's going on?
- Come on, Joe.

218
00:13:05.176 --> 00:13:07.596
- You were saying you were in love...
- No, I didn't say that.

219
00:13:07.606 --> 00:13:09.326
- Look, he really digs you.
- Joe, listen...

220
00:13:09.476 --> 00:13:11.635
He likes you, though. See you.

221
00:13:11.815 --> 00:13:13.905
I love my job.
I have an amazing job.

222
00:13:14.075 --> 00:13:15.475
Just this week, with the contest...

223
00:13:17.045 --> 00:13:20.455
...it's a little crazy. You really
have to be extra, extra attentive.

224
00:13:20.715 --> 00:13:23.815
When you have so many guys
in the water you can't miss a thing.

225
00:13:23.985 --> 00:13:27.655
But you know what? I have a perfect
record. I've never lost anybody.

226
00:13:27.865 --> 00:13:29.885
Sure, there have been close calls, but...

227
00:13:30.065 --> 00:13:32.655
- Help!
- Oh, Arnold. I turn my back for one...

228
00:13:32.835 --> 00:13:35.165
- Just lay some feeling on her.
- How do you mean?

229
00:13:35.335 --> 00:13:38.705
- Through words. Through touch.
- Walk me through the approach.

230
00:13:38.875 --> 00:13:41.235
- I'm Lani. You're me.
- You sure about that?

231
00:13:41.405 --> 00:13:44.465
- I get real serious.
- Let's not. Let's not.

232
00:13:44.645 --> 00:13:46.135
- Whoa.
- What is it?

233
00:13:46.675 --> 00:13:49.275
That's it! That's Big Z's shrine.

234
00:13:49.445 --> 00:13:52.845
- Remember?
- No, no. Not really.

235
00:13:54.255 --> 00:13:58.125
Today, the world of surfing
lost one of its legends.

236
00:13:58.295 --> 00:14:00.915
Big Z took his final ride this morning...

237
00:14:01.095 --> 00:14:05.585
...during a competition with
up-and-coming surfer Tank Evans.

238
00:14:06.165 --> 00:14:11.105
Z was last seen paddling into
a massive swell off Pen Gu Bay.

239
00:14:20.445 --> 00:14:24.845
Friends of Big Z gathered
to remember and celebrate his life.

240
00:14:27.215 --> 00:14:28.215
Great shot!

241
00:14:28.385 --> 00:14:29.855
What? Hey!

242
00:14:30.455 --> 00:14:33.284
- Every time.
- He's got a pretty good throwing fin.

243
00:14:33.454 --> 00:14:35.624
Stop doing... Stop it! Cut it out!

244
00:14:36.394 --> 00:14:39.294
- That's like three in a row.
- Here, give it a shot.

245
00:14:41.634 --> 00:14:45.864
What? Wait a minute. Look at this.

246
00:14:46.034 --> 00:14:48.474
- Don't. Stop it.
- It's a Big Z necklace.

247
00:14:48.644 --> 00:14:51.704
That's not funny. Stop.
Stop! What are you doing?

248
00:14:51.874 --> 00:14:54.004
Look, everybody, it's Big Z's last fan!

249
00:14:54.214 --> 00:14:56.074
Coming through.
Out of the way. Let's go.

250
00:14:56.244 --> 00:14:58.404
- You don't deserve to talk about him.
- He's a big zero.

251
00:14:58.414 --> 00:15:00.054
- Shut your mouth!
- Zero starts with "Z"!

252
00:15:00.084 --> 00:15:02.914
You'll never be as good as Big Z, Stank.

253
00:15:04.054 --> 00:15:07.614
Hey, hey, people, come on now.
Smile on your brother.

254
00:15:07.794 --> 00:15:12.124
- Keep your girlfriend out of this!
- You can't do that to my friend.

255
00:15:12.864 --> 00:15:15.804
You're getting quite a workout there.
That feels good.

256
00:15:15.964 --> 00:15:19.464
Why don't you work on my glutes
a little bit? That's very nice.

257
00:15:21.144 --> 00:15:25.164
- All right. That's enough, guys.
- I'll take you on anytime, anywhere.

258
00:15:25.344 --> 00:15:28.904
Well, then how about
right here, right now, huh?

259
00:15:29.084 --> 00:15:31.414
Hey, Mikey, get this kid a board!

260
00:15:31.584 --> 00:15:35.414
All right, who wants to see
the little guy take on the champ?

261
00:15:35.684 --> 00:15:37.244
Little guys rule!

262
00:15:37.424 --> 00:15:44.264
A little one-on-one surfing action
between Tank Evans and Jerry...

263
00:15:44.434 --> 00:15:46.194
- Cody. Cody.
- Cody Maverick.

264
00:15:46.534 --> 00:15:51.194
Cody Mavencourt. And the one
that rides the biggest wave wins.

265
00:16:03.083 --> 00:16:06.213
Are you nervous
about going against Tank Evans?

266
00:16:06.383 --> 00:16:08.813
Ah, Tank. Nervous?
What do I have to be nervous about?

267
00:16:28.273 --> 00:16:29.603
Give it up! Come on, now!

268
00:16:29.773 --> 00:16:31.603
I'm gonna chum the water with your head.

269
00:16:31.773 --> 00:16:35.043
- Bring it on, pecker face. Let's go.
- Pecker face?

270
00:16:39.313 --> 00:16:40.643
It's mine!

271
00:16:50.723 --> 00:16:52.663
So, Cody, when you take your first wave...

272
00:16:52.833 --> 00:16:55.293
...and the whole island's there
to watch, what'll it be like?

273
00:16:55.463 --> 00:16:58.303
It's gonna be amazing.
It'll be the best wave of my life.

274
00:16:58.473 --> 00:17:01.023
I hope the cameras are rolling
because you'll want to watch it...

275
00:17:01.033 --> 00:17:04.563
...over and over and over again.
It's gonna be awesome!

276
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:21.022
I can't look.

277
00:17:21.522 --> 00:17:25.122
- Poor kid. He's... Poor kid.
- Wow! That was spectacular!

278
00:17:28.332 --> 00:17:30.892
I'm number one! The Tank!

279
00:18:05.332 --> 00:18:08.792
We're trying to get the details.
The lifeguard just pulled him in.

280
00:18:12.312 --> 00:18:15.762
That's what happens
when you take on the Tank, right?

281
00:18:17.582 --> 00:18:18.772
Cody, Cody!

282
00:18:18.952 --> 00:18:21.612
- How is he? Okay? What can I do?
- Yeah, he's okay.

283
00:18:21.782 --> 00:18:26.782
I can help. Except if there's blood.
Just the thought of blood makes me...

284
00:18:27.592 --> 00:18:29.612
Somebody help the chicken.

285
00:18:29.792 --> 00:18:32.282
- Tank, you okay?
- Tank needs fuel.

286
00:18:32.792 --> 00:18:34.992
Mikey, get the board, will you?

287
00:18:35.502 --> 00:18:37.622
Come on. Come on. Come on.

288
00:18:41.971 --> 00:18:47.101
- Did I win? I won, huh?
- You should've stayed in Antarctica.

289
00:18:48.111 --> 00:18:50.171
- Oh, wow.
- You're gonna be okay.

290
00:18:50.341 --> 00:18:54.541
Look at that.
There's pixies everywhere.

291
00:18:56.021 --> 00:18:59.511
What do you think about Cody going
into a contest and possibly winning?

292
00:18:59.691 --> 00:19:00.711
- You know, I'm...
- Ha.

293
00:19:00.891 --> 00:19:04.651
- Why did you just laugh?
- Because he keeps saying "possible."

294
00:19:04.831 --> 00:19:09.261
Like it's "possible" that you're gonna
win. And you're gonna do anything.

295
00:19:09.431 --> 00:19:12.801
- Really, what are the chances?
- They're high. Aren't they high?

296
00:19:13.101 --> 00:19:17.161
I mean, they're normal chances.
It's not like I'm, like, the underdog.

297
00:19:27.781 --> 00:19:32.511
Hey, Geek! Geek!
Get up and help me.

298
00:19:32.821 --> 00:19:34.291
Geek.

299
00:19:35.061 --> 00:19:36.611
Geek?

300
00:19:38.491 --> 00:19:42.691
Geek. Wake up! I need your help.

301
00:19:43.201 --> 00:19:45.491
Come on. Get off your lazy butt
and come and help me.

302
00:19:45.671 --> 00:19:47.331
Beautiful dream.

303
00:19:47.501 --> 00:19:50.801
- Did you ever know Sheila?
- No. I don't know Sheila.

304
00:19:50.971 --> 00:19:52.941
- Wait, wait, wait. What?
- What?

305
00:19:53.111 --> 00:19:54.111
Who's this guy?

306
00:19:54.271 --> 00:19:57.001
- He's a surfer. He's hurt.
- Who are all those guys?

307
00:19:57.181 --> 00:19:59.301
They're with him. Ignore them.

308
00:19:59.481 --> 00:20:01.211
- Come on.
- Lani, what are you doing?

309
00:20:01.381 --> 00:20:03.541
If you help him, they'll go away.

310
00:20:03.721 --> 00:20:06.240
- Hey! Get out of here!
- Help him!

311
00:20:07.050 --> 00:20:09.750
- Where do you want him?
- Nowhere. That's the whole point.

312
00:20:09.920 --> 00:20:12.950
- No outsiders. Come on.
- I know, I know, I know.

313
00:20:13.130 --> 00:20:17.460
This is an emergency. He went down
bad over the falls. I don't know if he...

314
00:20:20.770 --> 00:20:22.630
- And did he hit the reef?
- I don't know.

315
00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:24.290
I'm not sure. I got him after...

316
00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:26.270
- What, is he your boyfriend?
- No. No.

317
00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:30.000
Wait, wait, wait.
Looks like he stepped on a fire urchin.

318
00:20:30.840 --> 00:20:34.340
Stepped on me? Are you kidding?
This guy was dancing on me.

319
00:20:35.680 --> 00:20:39.480
Just look at this. Broken, broken,
gone, gone, broken, broken, broken...

320
00:20:39.650 --> 00:20:44.490
This is pretty bad.
This is really bad.

321
00:20:45.560 --> 00:20:47.360
- What... Cody!
- I hurt.

322
00:20:47.530 --> 00:20:50.930
- You're gonna be okay. What?
- Maybe I shouldn't have taken that out.

323
00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:53.000
Poison's released. Wow. Amazing.

324
00:20:53.170 --> 00:20:55.600
- What's amazing?
- That you're still alive.

325
00:20:55.770 --> 00:20:59.970
It's all right. I'm gonna fix you up.
I can fix your foot just fine.

326
00:21:00.210 --> 00:21:03.900
- Where is it? I've been looking...
- It's a saw. You just threw a saw.

327
00:21:04.080 --> 00:21:08.840
Don't let him move like that. He's
pushing the poison all over his body.

328
00:21:09.020 --> 00:21:11.250
- Come on, come on.
- I know he looks...

329
00:21:11.890 --> 00:21:13.350
Here it is.

330
00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:16.410
- What are you doing?
- What is he doing?

331
00:21:16.590 --> 00:21:17.890
This is a sure-fire cure.

332
00:21:18.060 --> 00:21:22.020
I learned it from an old medicine
man. It, well, works wonders.

333
00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:24.290
- What? No! Not that!
- Not what?

334
00:21:24.500 --> 00:21:26.690
What is he gonna... Gonna what?

335
00:21:27.329 --> 00:21:28.799
- Come on, now.
- Geek, stop.

336
00:21:28.969 --> 00:21:32.409
Let's do this. Lani, can you make
some water sounds?

337
00:21:32.569 --> 00:21:34.869
- Oh, my gosh, this is so gross.
- What is water sounds?

338
00:21:35.039 --> 00:21:38.769
- Come on. Here we go.
- No, no, no. You...

339
00:21:42.749 --> 00:21:45.809
Kid, you better keep your mouth shut.
See, what'd I tell you?

340
00:21:45.989 --> 00:21:49.049
Hold his foot still, Lani. Come on.
Knock him out or something.

341
00:21:49.219 --> 00:21:51.379
- I'm running on empty here.
- I'm trying!

342
00:21:56.299 --> 00:21:59.129
So how you been?

343
00:22:00.169 --> 00:22:02.639
Wow, sea urchin in the foot.
That sounds pretty nasty.

344
00:22:02.799 --> 00:22:03.799
Yeah.

345
00:22:03.969 --> 00:22:05.669
How do you cure something like that?

346
00:22:06.909 --> 00:22:08.239
You pee on it.

347
00:22:09.039 --> 00:22:11.509
- That's disgusting.
- I know!

348
00:22:11.679 --> 00:22:15.079
Hey. How long am I stuck
with this guy?

349
00:22:15.249 --> 00:22:17.109
- Because you know...
- Till he's better.

350
00:22:17.279 --> 00:22:21.879
Well, come back soon and,
please, bring me some clams.

351
00:22:22.059 --> 00:22:23.579
- No.
- I'm running low here.

352
00:22:23.759 --> 00:22:26.479
I can't keep doing this. You've got
to start taking care of yourself.

353
00:22:26.589 --> 00:22:28.249
- Oh, come on.
- Bye.

354
00:22:28.729 --> 00:22:33.219
- Bring me some more clams!
- Okay.

355
00:22:43.109 --> 00:22:45.809
If it's just as well with you,
I don't want to talk about Cody.

356
00:22:45.979 --> 00:22:48.099
He lost. That's it.
That's his problem. It's not mine.

357
00:22:48.249 --> 00:22:50.249
Aren't you concerned
about anybody's well-being...?

358
00:22:50.278 --> 00:22:53.198
The kid's fine. He was born in water.
He's a penguin, for crying out loud!

359
00:22:53.218 --> 00:22:55.978
- Did you see that wave hit him?
- That's the whole idea of surfing.

360
00:22:56.158 --> 00:22:59.278
- I care. I care!
- Mikey! Wait till you see this.

361
00:23:00.228 --> 00:23:02.388
Look at those little legs.
Stick, stick, stick, sticky.

362
00:23:02.458 --> 00:23:04.928
It's the way I walk. I'm constantly...

363
00:23:05.098 --> 00:23:08.068
- Boom-chicka-chicka...
- What's with the "boom-chicka-boom"?

364
00:23:08.698 --> 00:23:12.498
I can't stand blood.
I can't stand the sight of blood.

365
00:23:12.668 --> 00:23:16.508
I can't stand...
sight of blood. Cody!

366
00:23:17.708 --> 00:23:22.238
- Dude, have you seen my friend Cody?
- No.

367
00:23:22.778 --> 00:23:25.618
Cody? Cody?

368
00:23:28.158 --> 00:23:29.378
He's not under there.

369
00:23:29.888 --> 00:23:32.688
Cody!

370
00:23:34.528 --> 00:23:35.858
How's it going, man?

371
00:23:39.398 --> 00:23:40.868
So I woke up this morning.

372
00:23:41.028 --> 00:23:45.438
I didn't know where I was. It's never
a good place to be when you wake up.

373
00:23:45.608 --> 00:23:47.798
Come on. Get up.

374
00:23:47.968 --> 00:23:49.668
- I don't want to.
- Breakfast.

375
00:23:49.838 --> 00:23:53.278
- Wakey, wakey. Come on.
- I don't want to.

376
00:23:54.508 --> 00:23:55.908
- How's your foot?
- My foot...

377
00:23:56.078 --> 00:24:00.178
- My foot's fine, but my head.
- Good. Good. Come on, kid. Get up.

378
00:24:00.918 --> 00:24:02.648
What the...?

379
00:24:04.058 --> 00:24:06.178
Yeah, I think I got a concussion.

380
00:24:09.728 --> 00:24:12.958
You should meet my brother, Glen.
You guys would really hit it off.

381
00:24:13.127 --> 00:24:18.627
Oh, no. No. Where's my necklace?
Did you see my necklace? It's gotta...

382
00:24:19.437 --> 00:24:20.797
No, no.

383
00:24:20.967 --> 00:24:24.097
Big deal. Get yourself another one
at Reggie's trinket shops.

384
00:24:24.307 --> 00:24:27.507
It's not just some necklace, guy.
He gave it to me himself.

385
00:24:27.677 --> 00:24:30.947
- Who?
- Big Z. When he came to Shiverpool.

386
00:24:31.117 --> 00:24:33.547
That guy believed in me
when no one else did.

387
00:24:33.717 --> 00:24:35.687
He told me never to give up
and to find a way...

388
00:24:35.857 --> 00:24:38.317
...because that's what winners do.
- What winners do. Yeah.

389
00:24:38.487 --> 00:24:41.047
It's funny, you know,
what a loser I became.

390
00:24:41.227 --> 00:24:45.527
Who cares what Big Z said?
You got to...

391
00:24:46.667 --> 00:24:51.327
...you know, do things your own way.
- I don't have a way.

392
00:24:53.207 --> 00:24:58.837
You do now. Just follow this.
It'll take you back to North Beach.

393
00:24:59.347 --> 00:25:02.207
Okay, nice to meet you.
Good luck.

394
00:25:11.087 --> 00:25:12.177
What do I do now?

395
00:25:12.357 --> 00:25:15.847
I can't show my face on the beach.
I can't go home.

396
00:25:18.297 --> 00:25:22.287
You always visualize where you're
gonna be, what you're gonna do.

397
00:25:26.007 --> 00:25:27.797
This ain't it.

398
00:25:56.396 --> 00:25:59.336
- What are you doing here?
- Here.

399
00:25:59.506 --> 00:26:03.406
- Oh, man. Thank you, man. This...
- Yeah.

400
00:26:03.576 --> 00:26:05.166
That's cool of you to come back.

401
00:26:05.346 --> 00:26:07.366
- Thank you.
- Better keep that knot tight.

402
00:26:07.546 --> 00:26:09.706
You lose it during a contest, it's a goner.

403
00:26:09.876 --> 00:26:13.476
Yeah, well, I'm not going
in any surf contests.

404
00:26:14.086 --> 00:26:19.576
Well, there's more to surfing
than beating Tank Evans, you know.

405
00:26:20.986 --> 00:26:22.286
Yeah.

406
00:26:22.496 --> 00:26:25.396
Look at that.
You know what you're sitting on there?

407
00:26:26.096 --> 00:26:27.856
That's koa wood.

408
00:26:28.026 --> 00:26:30.156
Best surfboards in the world
are made of that stuff.

409
00:26:30.336 --> 00:26:33.356
- Yeah?
- You got a koa board?

410
00:26:33.536 --> 00:26:39.306
- No, I don't have a "board" board.
- Well, you wanna...?

411
00:26:40.046 --> 00:26:41.566
You want to make one?

412
00:26:42.716 --> 00:26:44.236
- Nah.
- What?

413
00:26:44.416 --> 00:26:46.716
I come all the way back here
to give you the necklace...

414
00:26:46.886 --> 00:26:50.376
...and I'm offering to make you
a board and you say, "Nah."

415
00:26:50.556 --> 00:26:53.286
Get off your lazy butt.
We're making a board. Come on.

416
00:26:53.456 --> 00:26:55.326
- All right.
- It's gonna be the best board...

417
00:26:55.496 --> 00:26:56.516
...you ever had.

418
00:26:56.696 --> 00:26:58.246
- All right?
- Okay, man.

419
00:26:58.426 --> 00:26:59.485
Cody!

420
00:27:02.195 --> 00:27:03.285
That's cool.

421
00:27:03.635 --> 00:27:06.495
Joe, can you just tell us
why you're out here looking for Cody?

422
00:27:06.665 --> 00:27:09.035
You know, we've known
each other way back...

423
00:27:09.205 --> 00:27:14.075
...since, like, yesterday, I think it was.
We got a lot in common.

424
00:27:14.345 --> 00:27:16.405
I never really knew my father either.

425
00:27:22.715 --> 00:27:25.705
Why are you making surfboards
in the middle of the jungle anyway?

426
00:27:25.885 --> 00:27:28.375
I'm just trying to understand.
I don't get it.

427
00:27:28.555 --> 00:27:32.085
Forget the 20 questions.
Let's just get the board made.

428
00:27:32.495 --> 00:27:37.295
Okay, it's just...
Are you a surfer, or do you...?

429
00:27:39.905 --> 00:27:42.925
- Very funny.
- Less talk, more pushing. Come on.

430
00:27:43.535 --> 00:27:45.905
Why are we pushing it?
Why don't we just roll it?

431
00:27:46.745 --> 00:27:47.865
I'm sorry. I didn't mean...

432
00:27:48.045 --> 00:27:51.775
I didn't know your foot was there.
Are you okay? I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

433
00:27:51.945 --> 00:27:54.975
It's not like I intentionally did it.
I'm sorry.

434
00:27:57.015 --> 00:27:59.245
- Cody. The log!
- Yeah, I know!

435
00:28:00.885 --> 00:28:03.485
Geek! Stop, stop!

436
00:28:04.955 --> 00:28:08.695
Cody, grab the vine. Grab the vine!

437
00:28:10.335 --> 00:28:12.565
- Now, pull it.
- I'm trying!

438
00:28:12.735 --> 00:28:14.535
Pull!

439
00:28:19.175 --> 00:28:20.535
Cody!

440
00:28:21.814 --> 00:28:23.144
Geek!

441
00:28:23.844 --> 00:28:25.104
Cody!

442
00:28:31.514 --> 00:28:34.424
Oh, no, no, no.

443
00:28:36.894 --> 00:28:39.624
Help me up so I can kick your butt.

444
00:28:40.964 --> 00:28:45.364
- I thought I killed you. You okay?
- Next time, when I say don't roll the...

445
00:28:45.534 --> 00:28:47.664
Wait. What's that?

446
00:28:50.374 --> 00:28:54.334
Yeah, it's a beach.
Sand, water, sun.

447
00:28:54.544 --> 00:28:57.174
You seen one, you seen them all.
Let's get out of here.

448
00:28:57.344 --> 00:28:59.604
No, come on, man.
Let's go check it out.

449
00:29:04.854 --> 00:29:06.914
You think Cody and the Geek
are doing all right?

450
00:29:07.084 --> 00:29:09.814
Yeah. I hate to see him
living out there all alone.

451
00:29:09.994 --> 00:29:11.854
It'll be good for him
to have something to do.

452
00:29:24.534 --> 00:29:27.444
Hey. Somebody's old board shack.

453
00:29:35.084 --> 00:29:36.314
Look at this.

454
00:29:40.184 --> 00:29:42.124
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

455
00:29:42.994 --> 00:29:45.223
These are Big Z's boards.

456
00:29:45.393 --> 00:29:49.553
Yeah, these are Big Z's boards.
