- No, look. I want to have fun.

690
00:43:45.483 --> 00:43:47.753
- Okay.
- Do I need mints or something?

691
00:43:47.923 --> 00:43:50.893
- You tell me.
- No, you won't need mints.

692
00:43:51.623 --> 00:43:55.423
Z used to carry us up here on his
shoulders. We'd have so much fun.

693
00:43:55.593 --> 00:43:58.223
- It's one of my favorite spots.
- Really?

694
00:43:58.433 --> 00:44:01.333
- Boy, to be 8 years old again.
- What is this?

695
00:44:01.503 --> 00:44:03.493
You don't want to get all cut up, do you?

696
00:44:03.673 --> 00:44:05.003
Hold on. What are you doing?

697
00:44:05.173 --> 00:44:07.433
No, no, no. I'm out of here.
I'm better off...

698
00:44:18.953 --> 00:44:20.943
It's going down! No, no, no!

699
00:44:25.263 --> 00:44:29.323
- This is insane!
- Stop fighting it, Cody! Just let go!

700
00:44:31.433 --> 00:44:33.063
All right!

701
00:44:37.503 --> 00:44:40.173
Now I'm in front of you.
What's going on now?

702
00:44:40.343 --> 00:44:41.833
It's not a race!

703
00:44:50.623 --> 00:44:53.523
Okay, wait, don't take the left...
Cody!

704
00:44:58.192 --> 00:45:02.222
- Give up, slowpoke! It's over with now!
- Not for long!

705
00:45:02.562 --> 00:45:04.762
Give up now, sucker!

706
00:45:08.932 --> 00:45:12.272
- I beat you!
- Congratulations, you sure did.

707
00:45:12.442 --> 00:45:14.002
You should probably get out of there.

708
00:45:14.172 --> 00:45:16.532
Why is that? This stuff is...
Look at me. It's so beautiful.

709
00:45:16.612 --> 00:45:18.202
Look at it. What is this stuff?

710
00:45:18.382 --> 00:45:21.212
See those things up above you?
They're glowworms.

711
00:45:21.382 --> 00:45:25.842
So you're right beneath them.
Yeah, that's poop.

712
00:45:35.862 --> 00:45:39.632
You know how some stinks stink
and other stinks smell good?

713
00:45:39.802 --> 00:45:42.062
- Yeah.
- This is, like, a good stink.

714
00:45:42.232 --> 00:45:43.232
A good stink?

715
00:45:43.902 --> 00:45:45.632
Can I tell you something personal?

716
00:45:45.802 --> 00:45:48.162
We're in the shower together.
You can say whatever you want.

717
00:45:48.242 --> 00:45:52.682
I'm serious. I'm really, really
jealous of you.

718
00:45:52.852 --> 00:45:53.972
Why?

719
00:45:54.152 --> 00:45:58.012
I couldn't get Z off his butt
for the last 10 years...

720
00:45:58.182 --> 00:46:00.712
...and then you come along and...

721
00:46:00.892 --> 00:46:03.652
He must really think a lot of you.

722
00:46:03.822 --> 00:46:07.382
I don't know. I've been a jerk to him.
I don't know what he thinks.

723
00:46:07.562 --> 00:46:09.652
- You haven't.
- I have. I've been a jerk.

724
00:46:11.032 --> 00:46:14.402
- I have.
- Then go not be a jerk.

725
00:46:15.072 --> 00:46:16.832
What does it matter to you anyways?

726
00:46:17.002 --> 00:46:19.701
He's my uncle.
He's the only family I've got.

727
00:46:28.951 --> 00:46:30.351
Okay.

728
00:47:32.781 --> 00:47:34.511
Z? No.

729
00:47:35.181 --> 00:47:39.451
No, no, no, don't you do it.
Z, don't do it. No.

730
00:47:39.621 --> 00:47:41.481
- No.
- Let's see here.

731
00:47:41.651 --> 00:47:43.520
- I swear...
- It's stronger than I thought.

732
00:47:43.690 --> 00:47:47.020
...if you break it...
- Should've been broken by now.

733
00:47:47.190 --> 00:47:49.850
Come on! Come on!

734
00:47:53.630 --> 00:47:55.290
Look at that.

735
00:47:56.900 --> 00:48:00.530
That's the best place
in the world to be, in the tube.

736
00:48:00.710 --> 00:48:01.730
Really?

737
00:48:01.910 --> 00:48:06.310
Yeah. Better than winning,
the trophy, all that stuff.

738
00:48:07.150 --> 00:48:10.510
Tube riding
is the ultimate thing in surfing...

739
00:48:10.680 --> 00:48:12.880
...to ride inside the wave
and make it out of it.

740
00:48:13.050 --> 00:48:14.640
It's all we want to do every day.

741
00:48:14.820 --> 00:48:17.760
It's almost impossible to describe.

742
00:48:17.920 --> 00:48:19.860
There's nothing I can compare it to.

743
00:48:20.030 --> 00:48:24.490
It's a feeling that not too many people
will experience...

744
00:48:25.000 --> 00:48:26.660
...so it's special in that sense.

745
00:48:26.830 --> 00:48:28.200
Then you try to remember it.

746
00:48:28.370 --> 00:48:31.300
Like, "I wish I could remember that,"
or "I wish I could get that again."

747
00:48:31.470 --> 00:48:33.130
It's so addicting.

748
00:48:33.510 --> 00:48:37.340
Once you get inside
you never want to get out.

749
00:48:37.540 --> 00:48:43.000
- Wow. That's amazing.
- Yeah, man. Nothing like it.

750
00:48:43.180 --> 00:48:48.680
So, that aside, how many points
would you get for getting tubed?

751
00:48:48.890 --> 00:48:51.190
Like, what does it depend on
for the contest?

752
00:48:51.360 --> 00:48:53.590
- Points?
- What?

753
00:48:53.790 --> 00:48:56.280
You know who you sound like right now?

754
00:48:56.460 --> 00:48:58.220
I promote happiness!

755
00:48:58.400 --> 00:49:02.030
Can you see the happiness emanating
from me? What's wrong with you?

756
00:49:02.200 --> 00:49:04.030
- We're live.
- Good. Good.

757
00:49:04.200 --> 00:49:08.499
I have to say, I have no doubt
that this year's Big Z Memorial...

758
00:49:08.669 --> 00:49:10.009
...is gonna be the best ever.

759
00:49:11.409 --> 00:49:13.899
With the competition just one day away...

760
00:49:14.079 --> 00:49:18.569
...the excitement is definitely building
here on Pen Gu Island.

761
00:49:38.939 --> 00:49:42.299
That didn't take too long.
I feel lightheaded.

762
00:49:42.469 --> 00:49:43.699
So get this.

763
00:49:44.039 --> 00:49:48.099
On my search for Cody,
I bump into my hot tub buddies again.

764
00:49:49.449 --> 00:49:51.639
I get it. You guys look hungry.

765
00:49:51.819 --> 00:49:55.049
You've probably got
the munchies or something.

766
00:49:57.119 --> 00:49:59.389
Squidito on el stickito?

767
00:50:09.199 --> 00:50:13.069
Check it out! Dude,
have you seen my friend Cody?

768
00:50:13.239 --> 00:50:15.969
He's kind of like a penguin.

769
00:50:16.139 --> 00:50:19.239
He's got a lot of black on him,
a lot of white.

770
00:50:19.409 --> 00:50:22.899
- How did you learn how to surf?
- I saw Big Z do it, actually.

771
00:50:23.079 --> 00:50:24.979
I don't think you were born yet.

772
00:50:25.149 --> 00:50:27.549
- I wasn't?
- No, I don't think so.

773
00:50:27.819 --> 00:50:32.588
Lani? I like her when
she teaches us because...

774
00:50:32.758 --> 00:50:34.488
Smudge! Not another one!

775
00:50:34.658 --> 00:50:37.178
I think he really has to go
to the bathroom right now.

776
00:50:37.828 --> 00:50:39.558
What's next? The board is done.

777
00:50:39.728 --> 00:50:41.628
- The board is done?
- The board is done.

778
00:50:41.798 --> 00:50:45.698
- Well, let's do some training.
- Finally!

779
00:50:46.038 --> 00:50:49.128
- Can we get a shot of you...
- You've got to get it in a long shot.

780
00:50:50.178 --> 00:50:52.668
Hey, Z! Come on!

781
00:50:52.838 --> 00:50:54.938
- Where you going?
- I thought we were going to train.

782
00:50:54.948 --> 00:50:58.398
Not in the water. Jeez.
What are you thinking?

783
00:50:59.818 --> 00:51:02.948
- You want to surf like Big Z used to?
- Yeah.

784
00:51:03.118 --> 00:51:05.818
I've got some tests here
to figure out your potential.

785
00:51:05.988 --> 00:51:08.518
- Let's do it.
- No, put them on your eyes.

786
00:51:08.688 --> 00:51:11.178
- Like this.
- On my eyes.

787
00:51:13.898 --> 00:51:16.928
- Take it, Cody.
- Can we do some training, seriously?

788
00:51:17.098 --> 00:51:19.379
What are you talking about?
What do you think we're doing?

789
00:51:19.398 --> 00:51:21.478
Acting like nutjobs.
That's what I think we're doing.

790
00:51:21.608 --> 00:51:24.008
Yeah, good. You're learning!

791
00:51:24.178 --> 00:51:26.198
And a big set comes in.

792
00:51:28.578 --> 00:51:30.278
Wipeout!

793
00:51:30.618 --> 00:51:32.518
- That's it!
- Take it easy!

794
00:51:32.978 --> 00:51:34.578
This is getting ridiculous.

795
00:51:34.748 --> 00:51:36.188
- You having fun?
- I hate you.

796
00:51:37.288 --> 00:51:38.718
Big, you know, slow:

797
00:51:40.628 --> 00:51:43.718
He does this flip over the top.
All right, now you go.

798
00:51:45.828 --> 00:51:48.728
No joy, man. No joy. Fail.

799
00:51:49.698 --> 00:51:54.367
I'm starting to see it, man. I think
I know what you're talking about.

800
00:51:55.307 --> 00:51:58.367
That's great. As long as
we're all having fun, right?

801
00:51:58.637 --> 00:52:02.837
Z, wake up. Wake up, Z. Z!

802
00:52:11.457 --> 00:52:13.417
Hey, Z, breakfast!

803
00:52:15.427 --> 00:52:16.787
Not a chance.

804
00:52:17.127 --> 00:52:20.717
- Four, three, two...
- You gotta get up early in the morning...

805
00:52:21.297 --> 00:52:22.387
...one.

806
00:52:31.337 --> 00:52:32.337
That is fun.

807
00:52:32.507 --> 00:52:35.447
- You're having fun?
- I am. Yes. Now I am.

808
00:52:36.007 --> 00:52:37.207
Then, Cody...

809
00:52:37.377 --> 00:52:39.037
...you passed!
- What?

810
00:52:39.217 --> 00:52:41.707
You did it! You're ready! Let's surf!

811
00:52:41.887 --> 00:52:46.417
Don't play me, Z. We're surfing?
Yes! Yes!

812
00:52:57.097 --> 00:52:58.567
Hey, check it...

813
00:53:05.277 --> 00:53:07.397
I didn't know you could surf!

814
00:53:13.647 --> 00:53:14.876
Relax!

815
00:53:15.046 --> 00:53:18.746
Long, slow, smooth.

816
00:53:18.916 --> 00:53:20.756
- Like making the board!
- There you go.

817
00:53:20.926 --> 00:53:23.856
- All right. Okay.
- Feels good, yeah?

818
00:53:35.066 --> 00:53:39.936
- You're in the water, Z!
- Come on out. Get wet! Come on!

819
00:53:44.416 --> 00:53:48.106
Lani, thank you.

820
00:53:54.026 --> 00:53:55.786
Look at that!

821
00:54:08.906 --> 00:54:12.566
- Nice! That's it! Nice.
- Great ride!

822
00:54:37.935 --> 00:54:39.725
Big Z is back!

823
00:54:51.045 --> 00:54:53.515
This is what it's all about.

824
00:54:54.315 --> 00:54:56.835
What could be better than this?

825
00:55:23.715 --> 00:55:26.305
I need some help
on this landing for the high note

826
00:55:30.815 --> 00:55:33.615
Nice. Nice.

827
00:55:33.985 --> 00:55:36.085
- Is that the only song that you know?
- Pretty much.

828
00:55:36.255 --> 00:55:38.725
You want to hear it again?
It goes like this.

829
00:55:38.955 --> 00:55:41.625
No? Okay. I got you there, didn't I?

830
00:55:41.795 --> 00:55:45.455
I must say you were
quite amazing out there today.

831
00:55:45.635 --> 00:55:48.395
- You weren't so bad yourself, kiddo.
- Thanks to this guy.

832
00:55:49.235 --> 00:55:53.795
- I just pointed you in a direction.
- Question, Z.

833
00:55:54.975 --> 00:55:56.995
- Change your mind about the song?
- No, no, no.

834
00:55:57.175 --> 00:55:58.645
Here, it goes something like this...

835
00:55:58.815 --> 00:56:01.544
I was wondering if you could come
watch me ride tomorrow.

836
00:56:03.144 --> 00:56:05.544
Yeah, yeah. We'll both ride, man.

837
00:56:05.714 --> 00:56:10.384
- No, not just... In the contest.
- Contest? What contest?

838
00:56:10.554 --> 00:56:12.754
The Big Z Memorial.
Remember that one?

839
00:56:12.924 --> 00:56:14.554
I know I'm asking a lot...

840
00:56:14.724 --> 00:56:17.124
...but it would really, really be...

841
00:56:17.294 --> 00:56:20.424
...the biggest thing in the world
to me if you could come.

842
00:56:22.504 --> 00:56:25.334
- You still want to be a part of that?
- Absolutely.

843
00:56:25.904 --> 00:56:30.364
- Why do you want me there anyway?
- I thought you'd want to be there.

844
00:56:30.544 --> 00:56:33.514
- I don't know why it's a big deal.
- It's no big deal.

845
00:56:33.814 --> 00:56:35.614
Why won't you come?

846
00:56:35.844 --> 00:56:37.114
- I'm not coming.
- Why?

847
00:56:37.284 --> 00:56:39.084
- Give it a rest.
- It's getting cold, guys.

848
00:56:39.254 --> 00:56:40.814
- Tell me why you're hiding.
- Hiding?

849
00:56:40.984 --> 00:56:43.354
- Why are you hiding?
- I'll have to eat all this by myself.

850
00:56:43.524 --> 00:56:45.654
Why didn't you come back
after you fell off the wave?

851
00:56:46.724 --> 00:56:48.854
That wave.

852
00:56:50.694 --> 00:56:55.824
That last day, winning had
become everything to me.

853
00:56:56.164 --> 00:56:57.794
I knew I was gonna beat Tank.

854
00:56:59.104 --> 00:57:05.274
But then, you know,
he starts to surf circles around me.

855
00:57:05.444 --> 00:57:08.504
I saw what he was doing.
I couldn't do what he was doing.

856
00:57:09.314 --> 00:57:11.614
Times had changed.

857
00:57:12.714 --> 00:57:15.554
I didn't want to walk back
on that beach with all my fans there.

858
00:57:15.724 --> 00:57:20.184
A loser. Everyone looking
at Big Z, the loser, the has-been.

859
00:57:20.764 --> 00:57:22.424
So...

860
00:57:30.673 --> 00:57:33.573
Big Z's dead,
and that's how it's gonna stay.

861
00:57:34.203 --> 00:57:36.363
Let me play you that song.

862
00:57:37.573 --> 00:57:40.543
What about "never give up"?
What about "find a way"?

863
00:57:40.883 --> 00:57:45.813
- You're giving up. You're giving up!
- Yeah, I'm giving up. That's my way.

864
00:57:46.283 --> 00:57:49.553
- Giving up.
- I thought you were the one guy.

865
00:57:49.723 --> 00:57:52.693
You don't like it, find your own way.

866
00:57:54.463 --> 00:57:55.983
Leave me out of it.

867
00:57:56.793 --> 00:57:58.383
Leave me out of it.

868
00:58:25.953 --> 00:58:28.453
I messed up.
I'm just...

869
00:58:28.663 --> 00:58:30.653
I'm... not good.

870
00:58:31.063 --> 00:58:33.793
This is when I needed someone.
I needed him.

871
00:58:34.833 --> 00:58:37.733
It's hard enough losing one dad, but...

872
00:58:38.803 --> 00:58:41.233
- What do you mean by...?
- Nothing.

873
00:58:41.443 --> 00:58:43.733
Nothing, man. Forget it.

874
00:58:58.322 --> 00:59:00.622
Peaceful. Peaceful.
I'm in peace. I come in peace.

875
00:59:00.822 --> 00:59:01.982
- Cody!
- Joe!

876
00:59:02.392 --> 00:59:05.692
- I've been looking everywhere for you!
- You've been looking for me?

877
00:59:05.862 --> 00:59:08.692
I didn't lose you on the whale.
I'm not gonna lose you now.

878
00:59:08.862 --> 00:59:12.302
- Thank you. Seriously, thank you.
- Radical.

879
00:59:14.542 --> 00:59:17.002
They're starting!
Cody, we gotta go! Come on!

880
00:59:17.212 --> 00:59:18.672
Wait a minute. Joe?

881
00:59:18.842 --> 00:59:19.932
Surfers riding...

882
00:59:20.112 --> 00:59:23.132
I'm sorry. Watch this, dude.
I can speak their language.

883
00:59:27.052 --> 00:59:30.252
I totally need my board. I don't
know where it is. I gotta go find it.

884
00:59:30.422 --> 00:59:32.612
- I'll see you in the lineup.
- See you, Joe.

885
00:59:32.792 --> 00:59:35.312
- This is gonna be fun, huh?
- See you.

886
00:59:36.932 --> 00:59:40.622
The tenth annual Big Z
is about to get underway...

887
00:59:40.802 --> 00:59:43.592
...and, whoa, it is the day of days.

888
00:59:43.772 --> 00:59:46.962
Big mountainous bombs
marching into our coastline.

889
00:59:47.272 --> 00:59:50.902
Kelly Slater, on a danger level,
one to ten, give me a number.

890
00:59:51.072 --> 00:59:52.072
Twenty.

891
00:59:52.242 --> 00:59:54.272
- Wow. Rob?
- There'll be blood.

892
00:59:54.442 --> 00:59:56.382
I'm scared, and I'm in the booth!

893
00:59:57.352 --> 00:59:59.512
- What are you doing here?
- Mike.

894
00:59:59.682 --> 01:00:01.952
You're gonna kill yourself.
Don't do this to yourself.

895
01:00:02.122 --> 01:00:03.452
Look what happened last time.

896
01:00:04.152 --> 01:00:06.422
- It's good to see you back.
- Are you serious?

897
01:00:06.592 --> 01:00:08.112
You're gonna be a real crowd pleaser.

898
01:00:08.292 --> 01:00:10.621
I'm telling you,
these people are gonna eat you up.

899
01:00:10.791 --> 01:00:14.281
- I'll be expecting big things from you.
- Thank you.

900
01:00:14.461 --> 01:00:16.691
People, big announcement.
Cody Maverick, he's back.

901
01:00:16.861 --> 01:00:18.201
The Wipeout King is back...

902
01:00:18.371 --> 01:00:20.571
...and I'm gonna tell you,
start looking for the sharks.

903
01:00:20.641 --> 01:00:22.691
They'll be circling because
there's gonna be blood.

904
01:00:22.871 --> 01:00:24.301
Spectacular carnage today.

905
01:00:24.471 --> 01:00:28.411
Thank you! Reggie Belafonte. Little
guy, big hair, big thoughts, big heart.

906
01:00:37.291 --> 01:00:41.241
Look at this.
You're going down, snowflake.

907
01:00:42.421 --> 01:00:45.651
I'm gonna make you wish
you were never even hatched.

908
01:00:46.791 --> 01:00:49.321
You want to see my trophies?

909
01:00:58.941 --> 01:01:00.771
Arnold, no.

910
01:01:06.781 --> 01:01:09.771
About 24 surfers
battling their way out to the...

911
01:01:10.821 --> 01:01:13.621
Good golly! Make that 18.

912
01:01:16.891 --> 01:01:19.291
Rob, after such a heavy wipeout
earlier in the week...

913
01:01:19.461 --> 01:01:21.581
...what do you think is going
through Maverick's mind?

914
01:01:21.661 --> 01:01:25.661
He's gonna have to stay focused and
channel that energy into good places.

915
01:01:25.971 --> 01:01:27.631
When are you gonna get a life?

916
01:01:30.041 --> 01:01:31.800
You are a nobody.

917
01:01:33.070 --> 01:01:35.300
You should've stayed in Antarctica, kid.

918
01:01:59.870 --> 01:02:02.730
He made it! Yeah, good.

919
01:02:02.900 --> 01:02:06.770
What an amazing first ride
mind-blower from Maverick.

920
01:02:12.480 --> 01:02:14.140
Did you guys see that?

921
01:02:14.320 --> 01:02:17.410
Man. I thought I was gonna lose it,
and then I just...

922
01:02:18.650 --> 01:02:21.550
I just let go, you know.
I let go, and there it was.

923
01:02:22.820 --> 01:02:25.490
Wow, it's been an amazing day...

924
01:02:25.660 --> 01:02:27.650
...of shredding in less than
stellar conditions...

925
01:02:27.830 --> 01:02:30.760
...but I never would have guessed
our three finalists.

926
01:02:30.930 --> 01:02:33.060
Well, Sal, it's no surprise
that Tank Evans...

927
01:02:33.230 --> 01:02:36.330
...has just breezed his way
into the finals.

928
01:02:36.500 --> 01:02:40.800
And Cody Maverick, from a horrible
wipeout a few days ago to this.

929
01:02:43.180 --> 01:02:46.410
And Chicken Joe from Sheboygan.
Who would have guessed it?

930
01:02:47.050 --> 01:02:50.350
I have never seen a finals like this.

931
01:02:51.490 --> 01:02:54.110
- We're in the finals, Joe.
- No way! We get to surf some more?

932
01:02:54.289 --> 01:02:57.619
Isn't it exciting?
Look at that. This is great, huh?

933
01:02:57.889 --> 01:03:01.229
You know, you should know this.
The Tank loves you.

934
01:03:02.129 --> 01:03:04.559
Looks like this will be
the easiest year ever.

935
01:03:05.629 --> 01:03:08.659
No way. Cody, did you hear that?
It's gonna be easy.

936
01:03:09.399 --> 01:03:12.069
Are you loving this?

937
01:03:14.479 --> 01:03:16.409
So who would you like
to see win the trophy?

938
01:03:16.579 --> 01:03:19.169
It's not so important to me.

939
01:03:19.349 --> 01:03:22.009
Friends are better than anything
in the world.

940
01:03:22.179 --> 01:03:23.379
Friends are forever.

941
01:03:24.019 --> 01:03:27.319
Trophies, you never know
what they can have happen to them.

942
01:03:28.589 --> 01:03:31.419
- That was awesome, mate.
- Muy impresivo, my friend.

943
01:03:31.589 --> 01:03:32.919
Thank you, bro. Thanks.

944
01:03:33.689 --> 01:03:35.089
- Finals.
- Hey!

945
01:03:35.259 --> 01:03:37.929
Yeah. I know. I can't even...

946
01:03:38.869 --> 01:03:41.529
I think I can win this thing.
It's too much right now.

947
01:03:41.699 --> 01:03:44.189
- Well, that's all you came for.
- What?

948
01:03:44.369 --> 01:03:47.469
- What is that supposed to mean?
- You made it pretty clear last night...

949
01:03:47.639 --> 01:03:49.719
...that winning's more important
to you than Z or me.

950
01:03:49.879 --> 01:03:52.279
But, hey, maybe you'll get to take
your stupid trophy home.

951
01:03:52.449 --> 01:03:54.849
- Lani. Come on.
- Come here, you!

952
01:03:55.319 --> 01:03:56.649
How about this, huh?

953
01:03:56.819 --> 01:04:01.879
Let me tell you something. You win
this thing, we're going places!

954
01:04:02.089 --> 01:04:04.989
Look at this kid.
He is a champ!

955
01:04:14.569 --> 01:04:18.728
Tank, nine-time defending champion.
He will roll on you.

956
01:04:18.908 --> 01:04:22.398
Expect him to win this thing. It's
basically a contest for second place.

957
01:04:22.578 --> 01:04:27.238
First, I'm gonna take you down.
Then I'm gonna fry the chicken.

958
01:04:29.418 --> 01:04:32.318
That cloud looks just like a kitten.

959
01:04:45.828 --> 01:04:47.628
Maverick and Evans take off.

960
01:04:48.338 --> 01:04:49.358
Mine!

961
01:04:49.538 --> 01:04:51.868
And it's Evans dropping in.

962
01:04:54.638 --> 01:04:57.628
And Tank's playing games,
blocking Maverick's every move.

963
01:04:58.578 --> 01:05:00.098
Maverick sticks a rail.

964
01:05:01.318 --> 01:05:06.008
Tank Evans down!
I have never, ever seen this before!

965
01:05:07.988 --> 01:05:09.478
But I'd love to see it again.

966
01:05:09.658 --> 01:05:13.288
Cody trying to take back the wave
that Tank snaked from him.

967
01:05:13.458 --> 01:05:15.758
Evans toying with him,
not paying attention.

968
01:05:15.928 --> 01:05:18.158
And there's the outside rail.
Evans goes down.

969
01:05:18.328 --> 01:05:22.858
And it's Maverick with this new-school
move. We'll call it "The Maverick."

970
01:05:28.678 --> 01:05:31.838
And look at this.
Maverick scoring big.

971
01:05:32.908 --> 01:05:37.348
Oh, it's so cute.
It's got little paws and the whiskers.

972
01:05:40.317 --> 01:05:43.147
Chicken Joe with a no-paddle drop-in!

973
01:05:44.827 --> 01:05:47.657
- Here we go!
- Nobody needs to help this chicken.

974
01:05:48.697 --> 01:05:49.917
I'm flying!

975
01:05:51.497 --> 01:05:56.597
Maverick and Joe tied, and no score
for Tank Evans? Unbelievable.

976
01:05:58.207 --> 01:06:02.067
Surfers, this is your final wave!

977
01:06:02.237 --> 01:06:06.577
- Joe, this is it. This wave wins it.
- Yeah, man!

978
01:06:08.577 --> 01:06:12.917
This wave is stacking up
to be a beautiful tube.

979
01:06:13.547 --> 01:06:16.787
Maverick should score big on this one!

980
01:06:18.627 --> 01:06:20.957
But wait! Evans drops in.

981
01:06:21.127 --> 01:06:24.717
It looks like Evans
is gonna take out the chicken.

982
01:06:30.137 --> 01:06:31.467
What's Maverick doing?

983
01:06:31.637 --> 01:06:34.537
- Go, Joe, go!
- Got it! Let's go!

984
01:06:34.707 --> 01:06:37.607
I don't believe this.
This contest was Maverick's to win.

985
01:06:37.807 --> 01:06:41.537
Now Evans pushing Maverick out
of bounds and into The Boneyards.

986
01:06:54.257 --> 01:06:57.087
- Tank, look out!
- You look out!

987
01:07:32.466 --> 01:07:33.466
Code!

988
01:07:35.996 --> 01:07:36.996
Z!

989
01:07:41.136 --> 01:07:43.036
- Cody, come on.
- Z!

990
01:07:43.206 --> 01:07:46.976
Paddle! Come on! Dig! Faster!
Come on. Dig!

991
01:07:48.216 --> 01:07:50.616
Don't dig! Don't dig!

992
01:07:50.786 --> 01:07:51.876
What?

993
01:07:52.546 --> 01:07:55.076
Let the wave carry you!

994
01:07:55.716 --> 01:07:57.376
You're gonna have to time it!

995
01:07:57.926 --> 01:08:01.046
You're gonna come right here, right to me!

996
01:08:04.596 --> 01:08:06.586
Five... four...

997
01:08:06.826 --> 01:08:09.426
Three... two... one.

998
01:08:14.506 --> 01:08:15.976
Z!

999
01:08:31.255 --> 01:08:32.815
Where's Cody?

1000
01:08:37.195 --> 01:08:39.255
Don't touch it! Don't touch that!

1001
01:08:39.425 --> 01:08:42.525
This is a reminder of the young surfer...

1002
01:08:42.695 --> 01:08:47.765
...who gave his life
for the sport he loved.

1003
01:08:51.975 --> 01:08:53.775
There you are.

1004
01:08:58.545 --> 01:09:01.845
I can't believe it! I can't believe it.

1005
01:09:03.055 --> 01:09:04.385
You came back.

1006
01:09:04.885 --> 01:09:07.545
You saved my life, man.
Thank you.

1007
01:09:07.725 --> 01:09:11.095
Hey, hey, come on.
You're gonna tip us!

1008
01:09:12.925 --> 01:09:15.555
Well, I lost.

1009
01:09:17.235 --> 01:09:18.925
Me too.

1010
01:09:21.075 --> 01:09:24.065
Come on. Let's go, loser.

1011
01:09:24.905 --> 01:09:26.275
You want to help me out here?

1012
01:09:26.445 --> 01:09:31.575
You know the routine. Come on. Long.
That's it. Smooth, you know. Come on.

1013
01:09:31.915 --> 01:09:36.905
Young Joey MacEnroe
was a beacon for a new generation.

1014
01:09:37.085 --> 01:09:40.055
May he rest in peace.

1015
01:09:41.955 --> 01:09:45.015
So, what am I bid for the board?
Who'll give me 30? 30, come on.

1016
01:09:45.195 --> 01:09:47.476
- Don't touch his stuff, man.
- Pal, if you want to bid...

1017
01:09:47.535 --> 01:09:49.724
- Give me that.
- Hey...!

1018
01:09:55.474 --> 01:09:57.204
Hey. Hey, everyone.

1019
01:09:58.204 --> 01:10:00.504
- How you been?
- Oh, my gosh!

1020
01:10:00.704 --> 01:10:02.874
- Yeah...
- Hey, man, that's Z.

1021
01:10:03.074 --> 01:10:04.634
...that's me.

1022
01:10:04.814 --> 01:10:07.044
Skank, what's happening, man?

1023
01:10:07.214 --> 01:10:09.874
Got a little sand
in your egg sac there, fella.

1024
01:10:10.054 --> 01:10:12.384
- Where have you been, Z?
- What happened?

1025
01:10:13.254 --> 01:10:14.584
Oh, you know...

1026
01:10:16.554 --> 01:10:21.554
...I got lost for a little while.
But that kid there, Cody...

1027
01:10:22.764 --> 01:10:25.594
...he pointed the way back.

1028
01:10:36.444 --> 01:10:38.764
Could you please shut that off?
Could you give me a minute?

1029
01:10:45.024 --> 01:10:46.954
Check it out! How about this?

1030
01:10:47.124 --> 01:10:49.594
You want to talk about talent scout?
People find talent.

1031
01:10:49.794 --> 01:10:55.454
I bring them back from the dead.
The now living legend, ladies and...

1032
01:10:55.634 --> 01:10:56.964
- Shut up.
- What? Shut up?

1033
01:10:57.134 --> 01:11:01.124
I'm not a legend. I'm a guy looking for
some nice waves, some good friends.

1034
01:11:01.634 --> 01:11:05.264
Hey, guys, the swell is happening
over on the north shore!

1035
01:11:05.444 --> 01:11:06.804
I'm right behind you, Z.

1036
01:11:06.974 --> 01:11:08.304
Ouch, that hurt.

1037
01:11:10.444 --> 01:11:14.713
Come back here!
You don't just walk away! Come on!

1038
01:11:16.083 --> 01:11:17.453
He's taking this loss pretty hard.

1039
01:11:17.623 --> 01:11:20.583
Tank, how does it feel
to lose after nine time...

1040
01:11:22.223 --> 01:11:25.453
I wasn't kissing her.
You can't have her!

1041
01:11:28.993 --> 01:11:29.993
Can we get a few words?

1042
01:11:30.163 --> 01:11:32.823
You gave up the trophy to help Joe.
What's that about?

1043
01:11:33.003 --> 01:11:35.903
You know, Rob, that's what friends do.

1044
01:11:36.073 --> 01:11:39.193
- How's it feel to win, Joe?
- I won?

1045
01:11:39.373 --> 01:11:42.673
Come on! I'll tell my mom.
Gimme. Gimme!

1046
01:11:44.343 --> 01:11:47.213
Oh, Lia! Oh, Lia.

1047
01:11:47.383 --> 01:11:50.973
Don't you walk away from me!
I am Reggie Belafon...

1048
01:11:52.483 --> 01:11:56.013
Turn that thing off.
Mikey! You are so fired!

1049
01:11:56.623 --> 01:11:59.253
I can't imagine a better day.

1050
01:12:05.433 --> 01:12:09.423
Dude, this... This whole
experience has just been...

1051
01:12:09.633 --> 01:12:12.533
It's amazing. Z?

1052
01:12:12.703 --> 01:12:17.613
I don't think I've ever had
a better friend to me in my life.

1053
01:12:17.783 --> 01:12:21.443
It's just really cool
to have everything I need.

1054
01:12:22.313 --> 01:12:24.783
- Don't do it. Help!
- Arnold!

1055
01:12:24.953 --> 01:12:28.353
To be honest, man, I'm kind of, like,
bored of talking about myself.

1056
01:12:28.523 --> 01:12:32.183
So, is that cool?
You guys got what you need?

1057
01:12:32.363 --> 01:12:34.652
- We got it.
- All right. Be good!

1058
01:12:43.272 --> 01:12:44.792
Cowabunga!

1059
01:13:52.842 --> 01:13:54.772
Of course we're proud of him!

1060
01:13:54.942 --> 01:13:56.772
What mother wouldn't be proud of him?

1061
01:13:56.942 --> 01:13:59.201
We're so full of proudness.

1062
01:13:59.381 --> 01:14:01.281
You know what?
He followed his dream...

1063
01:14:01.451 --> 01:14:05.211
...and he went out there, and now
he's coming home with the trophy.

1064
01:14:05.381 --> 01:14:07.371
I can't wait to see his trophy.

1065
01:14:07.551 --> 01:14:09.541
There's not really a trophy.

1066
01:14:10.291 --> 01:14:12.721
Is there, like, a big shell
or something like that?

1067
01:14:12.891 --> 01:14:15.621
There's no shell. There's no trophy.
Well, he didn't win.

1068
01:14:15.791 --> 01:14:16.821
What?

1069
01:14:17.191 --> 01:14:20.191
How bad was it?
Did he get smoked?

1070
01:14:20.401 --> 01:14:23.561
- He was in the finals.
- Second place? That's losing.

1071
01:14:23.731 --> 01:14:26.071
- Winning is not everything, Glen.
- Right.

1072
01:14:26.241 --> 01:14:27.731
Look at what Cody did...

1073
01:14:27.911 --> 01:14:30.071
Go back to the
"winning isn't everything" thing.

1074
01:14:30.311 --> 01:14:32.571
That doesn't compute, really.

1075
01:14:32.741 --> 01:14:38.241
You know what, Glen? I really hope
someday you can be more like Cody.

1076
01:14:38.721 --> 01:14:40.181
This interview is over.

